On Wednesday, Islamabad denied violating the ceasefire in Kashmir, a region that has sparked wars between India and Pakistan.
Indian police reported mortar fire from Pakistan into India's Durga Post area.
The ceasefire, in place since 2003, faces scrutiny as tensions rise.
Despite ongoing conflicts, a bus service between the two zones of Kashmir is set to resume, symbolizing progress in peace talks.
Emotional reunions across the Neelum River highlight the desire for unity.
Indian Prime Minister Singh's visit to Kashmir signals efforts to end separatist violence.
The bus service revival after 50 years offers hope for reconciliation in the region.
